        <h2 class="title" data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="zoom-out" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">The issue.</h2>
        <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back">Compared with other universities around the country, our voting rate is down. This on top of the fact that the underrepresentation of college students is experienced widely across the country, not to mention how that compounds with issues of socio-economic status. According to
            <a class="link" href="assets/General-Election-NSLVE-Data.pdf" target="_blank">our campus report</a>
            from the National Study of Learning, Voting, and Education, less than half of UVM's undergraduate students voted in the last general election.</p>

        <p data-sal-repeat="data-sal-repeat" data-sal="slide-right" data-sal-duration="1000" data-sal-easing="ease-out-back" class="bold">We can fix this.</p>
